.TH SWAPTERM(1),User Commands,SWAPTERM(1)

.SH NAME
swapterm - multi-terminal console multiplexer

.SH SYNOPSIS
swapterm

.SH DESCRIPTION
swapterm takes over the system CHROUT hook and general hook 1 and presents up to four virtual terminals sharing the screen.
Each running process is bound to one of the four terminals, and only the currently displayed terminal is rendered;
the others remain live but hidden.

swapterm allocates an extended-memory bank as a ring buffer for incoming CHROUT bytes, and a second as per-process line buffers.
Output from every process is tagged with its PID, buffered, and then drawn into the VERA tilemap associated with that process's assigned terminal.

The program runs until it is killed.

.SH HOOK 1 PROTOCOL
Other programs control the multiplexer by sending two-byte messages on general hook 1:

byte 0: target PID

byte 1: command

If command is 0..3, the target process is reassigned to that terminal index.
If command is 4..7, the currently displayed terminal is switched to index (command - 4);
the PID byte is ignored in this case.

.SH DIAGNOSTICS
swapterm exits with status 1 if:

- the VERA register lock cannot be acquired (another program owns it)

- the CHROUT hook is already in use

- general hook 1 is already in use

No error message is printed.

.SH EXIT STATUS
0: Normal exit (not reachable from the main loop - swapterm runs until killed).

1: A required hook or VERA lock could not be claimed.

.SH SEE ALSO
kill(1), ps(1)
